import matplotlib
import seaborn
# 
def plot_distribution(df, cols=5, width=15, height=15, hspace=0.2, wspace=0.5):
    import math
    #help(plt.style.use)
    print(matplotlib.__version__)
    print(seaborn.__version__)
    sns.set_style("whitegrid")
    #plt.style.use('seaborn-whitegrid')     #
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(width,height))  #figure
    fig.subplots_adjust(left=None, bottom=None, right=None, top=None, wspace=wspace, hspace=hspace) # 
    rows = math.ceil(float(df.shape[1]) / cols)    # ceil
    for i, column in enumerate(df.columns):       #
        ax = fig.add_subplot(rows, cols, i + 1)         # subplotax
        ax.set_title(column)                            # 
        if df.dtypes[column] == object:        # ,
            g = sns.countplot(y=column, data=df)   #np.objectcountploty
            plt.xticks(rotation=25) 
        else:
            g = sns.distplot(df[column])   #np.object 
            plt.xticks(rotation=25)
